1
00:00:18,940 --> 00:00:23,880
笙ｪOnly after bloom comes fruit笙ｪ

2
00:00:25,290 --> 00:00:29,260
笙ｪWho says glory must fade to the past笙ｪ

3
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:37,010
笙ｪOnly through thunder
do you reach the clouds笙ｪ

4
00:00:38,210 --> 00:00:43,120
笙ｪWho made you the crown of every peak笙ｪ

5
00:00:44,650 --> 00:00:47,930
笙ｪI stand at the center of the stage笙ｪ

6
00:00:47,930 --> 00:00:51,000
笙ｪMy shadow is pinned against the wall笙ｪ

7
00:00:51,710 --> 00:00:56,660
笙ｪFacing the light earns every medal笙ｪ

8
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:00,880
笙ｪLittle birds,
save your needless pecking笙ｪ

9
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:04,160
笙ｪThe open sky rises high笙ｪ

10
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:09,830
笙ｪWhen night falls,
the moon begins to shine笙ｪ

11
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:13,860
笙ｪI stand in the heart of these lands笙ｪ

12
00:01:13,860 --> 00:01:17,220
笙ｪMy shadow bears no crown or robe笙ｪ

13
00:01:17,630 --> 00:01:23,300
笙ｪThen I know truth needs no disguise笙ｪ

14
00:01:23,710 --> 00:01:26,960
笙ｪThe green hills see me as I am笙ｪ

15
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:30,290
笙ｪLike dew, lightning,
and moon on the river笙ｪ

16
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:34,730
笙ｪShowing me exactly who I am笙ｪ

17
00:01:34,730 --> 00:01:35,980
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 4=

19
00:01:39,320 --> 00:01:40,160
Who's looking for me?

20
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:42,960
Who wants Hu Sanyuan?

21
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:49,880
Hu Sanyuan.

22
00:01:53,380 --> 00:02:00,380
笙ｪThe red star shines and points the way笙ｪ

23
00:02:02,440 --> 00:02:03,560
So you're Hu Sanyuan.

24
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:06,960
You're the one I'm hitting.

25
00:02:10,620 --> 00:02:13,400
笙ｪThe red star is twinkling笙ｪ

26
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:14,240
I'll go take a look.

27
00:02:14,980 --> 00:02:19,380
笙ｪThe red star warms our hearts笙ｪ

28
00:02:19,380 --> 00:02:23,420
笙ｪFollowing Chairman Mao and the Party笙ｪ

29
00:02:23,420 --> 00:02:26,860
笙ｪThe shining red star lives on笙ｪ

30
00:02:26,860 --> 00:02:27,700
What happened?

31
00:02:27,700 --> 00:02:28,560
Is it him?

32
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:30,200
How did he end up this badly hurt?

33
00:02:31,280 --> 00:02:32,360
What happened here?

34
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:35,000
Who did this?

35
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:35,960
Who?

36
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:37,080
Stop yelling.

37
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:38,320
They already ran off.

38
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:43,600
Who did this to you?

39
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:55,000
Hu Sanyuan was first taken away
by the police

40
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:57,640
and then beaten up.

41
00:02:58,160 --> 00:03:01,480
It made this mountain kid fear

42
00:03:01,640 --> 00:03:04,680
this strange city world even more.

43
00:03:08,499 --> 00:03:09,692
Let's report it to the police.

44
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:10,960
Report what?

45
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:12,720
It's not my first time.

46
00:03:16,760 --> 00:03:18,640
Don't be scared. I'm okay.

47
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:20,440
Just some minor cuts and bruises.

48
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,240
Still, you can't just take

49
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:23,200
a beating for no reason.

50
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:24,640
Forget it.

51
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:27,880
Take her back and practice singing.

52
00:03:27,880 --> 00:03:29,440
She has to practice.

53
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:30,640
I'm heading out.

54
00:03:30,651 --> 00:03:31,927
(Hospital)
Where are you going?

55
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:32,840
To find someone.

56
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,640
Let's go.

57
00:03:41,640 --> 00:03:42,480
Seize the reform.

58
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:44,080
Boost production.

59
00:03:44,760 --> 00:03:47,160
Advance people's thinking.

60
00:03:47,840 --> 00:03:49,640
Drive production forward.

61
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:07,560
Qin Feng.

62
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:09,880
You two, come back later.

63
00:04:13,040 --> 00:04:13,880
What?

64
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:16,600
Who hit you?

65
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:18,360
If I knew who did it,

66
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:19,360
I wouldn't be asking you.

67
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:21,080
What happened?

68
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:22,760
At the cinema just now,

69
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:23,760
someone jumped me.

70
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:25,760
You must've crossed someone.

71
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:27,560
Ask around for me.

72
00:04:27,560 --> 00:04:28,400
See who did it.

73
00:04:34,280 --> 00:04:35,120
Si.

74
00:04:36,440 --> 00:04:37,280
Si!

75
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:38,760
Come here.

76
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:47,920
Hu Sanyuan got jumped

77
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:48,840
at the cinema.

78
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:51,040
Go into town and see who did it.

79
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:54,320
Then what?

80
00:04:54,640 --> 00:04:55,480
That's it.

81
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:57,640
Just find out who did this for me.

82
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:59,026
Don't worry about the rest.

83
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:00,240
Go. Now.

84
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,000
Stop acting tough.

85
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,653
You don't even know who hit you.

86
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:13,400
How am I acting tough?

87
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:19,040
Where's my uncle?

88
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:20,680
Forget about him for now.

89
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:22,880
Think about yourself first.

90
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:26,360
Now, picture yourself as Pan Dongzi.

91
00:05:26,840 --> 00:05:30,240
Then sing out bravely, like him.

92
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:32,240
Sing with me.

93
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:36,630
笙ｪThe red star is twinkling笙ｪ

94
00:05:36,630 --> 00:05:37,510
Sing.

95
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,840
Where did my uncle go?

96
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:45,290
笙ｪThe red star is twinkling笙ｪ

97
00:05:45,290 --> 00:05:46,150
Sing.

98
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:47,680
I want to go home.

99
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:50,720
Why are you giving up so easily?

100
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:53,840
This chance hardly ever comes.

101
00:05:53,840 --> 00:05:55,360
Just sing now.

102
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:56,240
Where are you going?

103
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:57,160
Laidi.

104
00:05:58,520 --> 00:05:59,400
Get back here.

105
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:01,600
Where are you running off to?

106
00:06:02,960 --> 00:06:05,880
Laidi, get back here.

107
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:09,040
Stop her.

108
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:10,720
Why run? Come here.

109
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:12,040
Come here.

110
00:06:12,320 --> 00:06:13,340
Let go of me.

111
00:06:13,340 --> 00:06:14,200
What are you doing?

112
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:15,306
I don't want to study opera.

113
00:06:15,520 --> 00:06:16,560
I want to go home.

114
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:17,920
What happened?

115
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:19,400
I can't teach her anymore.

116
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:20,920
Whoever wants to can teach her.

117
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:26,040
笙ｪThe red star is twinkling笙ｪ

118
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:30,240
笙ｪThe red star warms our hearts笙ｪ

119
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:31,640
Sing.

120
00:06:37,920 --> 00:06:40,440
Did seeing me get hit scare you?

121
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:42,120
Don't be scared.

122
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:43,260
Without a few blows,

123
00:06:43,260 --> 00:06:44,750
a man will never grow up. Got it?

124
00:06:44,750 --> 00:06:46,800
When we're kids,
our parents set us straight;

125
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:49,680
when we grow up, life does it out there.

126
00:06:50,320 --> 00:06:52,160
Every hard knock makes us grow a bit.

127
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:54,920
A pumpkin won't ripen
without some frost.

128
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:57,713
You'll understand that
when you're older.

129
00:06:58,880 --> 00:07:01,600
Tomorrow is your first real battle.

130
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:04,000
I've got your back.

131
00:07:04,520 --> 00:07:05,840
You just go up front and sing.

132
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:07,560
Leave the rest to me.

133
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:09,120
The two of us together,

134
00:07:09,640 --> 00:07:11,040
let's win this one, okay?

135
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:13,480
Sing with me.

136
00:07:14,840 --> 00:07:18,520
笙ｪThe red star is twinkling笙ｪ

137
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:21,600
笙ｪThe red star warms our hearts笙ｪ

138
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:22,480
Sing.

139
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:36,480
笙ｪThe red star is twinkling笙ｪ

140
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:41,480
笙ｪThe red star is twinkling笙ｪ

141
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:45,720
笙ｪThe red star warms our hearts笙ｪ

142
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:46,560
That's it.

143
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:48,280
There you go.

144
00:07:48,280 --> 00:07:51,000
Come on, sing. Loud now.

145
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:52,360
Alright, ready, sing.

146
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:57,000
笙ｪThe red star is twinkling笙ｪ

147
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,800
笙ｪThe red star笙ｪ

148
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:11,040
Go back first.

149
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:13,160
Where are you going?

150
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:14,200
I'm heading out.

151
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:24,520
You idiot.

152
00:08:25,360 --> 00:08:26,800
So, it really was you.

153
00:08:31,280 --> 00:08:32,880
How'd you end up this messed up?

154
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:35,320
He was hit by his standard for you.

155
00:08:35,880 --> 00:08:37,680
You two are just as bad.

156
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:40,600
I told you to find the person.

157
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:41,726
Don't worry about the rest.

158
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:43,160
Si didn't listen.

159
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:48,720
I'm telling you.
That beating was for nothing.

160
00:08:49,040 --> 00:08:51,160
I'm still mad about it.

161
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:54,800
If you're really a man, do it openly.

162
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:55,920
Let's settle it one-on-one.

163
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:57,880
Getting people to attack in secret

164
00:08:58,280 --> 00:08:59,720
is just plain spineless.

165
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:00,960
You got people involved too.

166
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:03,680
Only because you started it first.

167
00:09:04,280 --> 00:09:05,120
Just look at this.

168
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:06,240
Then what about mine?

169
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:07,080
And this too.

170
00:09:07,280 --> 00:09:08,120
You deserve it.

171
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:32,760
Why are you sitting here?

172
00:09:38,280 --> 00:09:39,120
What's that?

173
00:09:39,640 --> 00:09:40,480
Rock sugar.

174
00:09:42,360 --> 00:09:43,520
My dad gave it to me.

175
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:45,800
Is it sweet?

176
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:51,300
What are you looking at?

177
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:53,280
The Big Dipper.

178
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:55,800
I told you to sing Red Star.

179
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:58,400
Why look at the Big Dipper?

180
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:01,600
You can see it from Jiuyangou too.

181
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:04,360
Of course. It's the same sky.

182
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,320
No.

183
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:08,200
It's brighter in Jiuyangou.

184
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:14,040
I don't want to sing.

185
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:16,720
I want to go home.

186
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:19,440
Why don't you want to sing?

187
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:21,600
This place feels like a sheep pen.

188
00:10:22,920 --> 00:10:24,000
I'm like one of the sheep.

189
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:29,640
Then who's the shepherd?

190
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:45,000
Ride slower.

191
00:10:45,640 --> 00:10:47,680
My head and butt are killing me.

192
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:49,960
You...

193
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:04,800
What are you doing?

194
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:06,840
Come on, no one's here.

195
00:11:07,920 --> 00:11:09,293
I'll give you a chance to get even.

196
00:11:09,680 --> 00:11:10,880
Just the two of us, one-on-one.

197
00:11:10,880 --> 00:11:12,200
Are you out of your mind?

198
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:13,360
You won't move, huh?

199
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:14,720
No.

200
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:16,120
Don't say I gave you no chance.

201
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:18,280
We're even now, one to one.

202
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:21,160
So, let's drop this whole thing.

203
00:11:21,760 --> 00:11:22,680
Now, the next thing.

204
00:11:23,560 --> 00:11:24,400
What thing?

205
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:27,080
My niece's trainee exam.

206
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:28,240
What to do about it?

207
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:29,400
Nothing. Let it be.

208
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:30,960
You have to help with this.

209
00:11:31,280 --> 00:11:32,560
I can't help you.

210
00:11:32,571 --> 00:11:33,264
Why not?

211
00:11:33,413 --> 00:11:34,413
Why not?

212
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:37,480
You act way too smug.

213
00:11:37,480 --> 00:11:39,200
Fine, ignore me if you want.

214
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:42,360
But you also slighted Huang Zhengjing.

215
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:43,640
If I help you with this,

216
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:45,080
I'd be offending Huang Zhengjing.

217
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:46,280
Why should I help you?

218
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:47,880
Aren't you afraid of crossing me?

219
00:11:47,880 --> 00:11:48,720
Nope.

220
00:11:49,560 --> 00:11:50,640
Come on, man.

221
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:53,120
Help me out this time,

222
00:11:53,640 --> 00:11:54,960
and I'll owe you one.

223
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:56,440
Next time you need something,

224
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:58,040
I'll return the favor, okay?

225
00:11:58,880 --> 00:12:00,480
I'm asking you this time, alright?

226
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:02,840
What good is asking me?

227
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:06,040
Huang Zhengjing has the final say.

228
00:12:06,040 --> 00:12:07,320
Go ask Huang Zhengjing.

229
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:09,800
Man, you won't budge either way.

230
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:11,760
I'm telling the truth.

231
00:12:13,160 --> 00:12:14,040
Go, go, go.

232
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:18,160
You usually seem pretty sharp,

233
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:19,786
but now you're acting like a fool.

234
00:12:20,040 --> 00:12:22,000
You're not even as sharp as your niece.

235
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:30,560
What do you mean?

236
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:32,600
Even your niece knows this:

237
00:12:33,280 --> 00:12:35,080
Strike a snake at its vital spot.

238
00:12:35,680 --> 00:12:36,520
What vital spot?

239
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:40,760
The kid
of Huang Zhengjing's wife's brother

240
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:42,800
is also trying for our trainee class.

241
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:44,800
That kid's even more clueless

242
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:46,000
than your niece.

243
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:47,680
He can't even speak clearly.

244
00:12:48,080 --> 00:12:49,360
Huang Zhengjing wouldn't agree,

245
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:53,840
so his wife kept making a scene
with that anonymous letter.

246
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:55,640
Huang Zhengjing is in a bind.

247
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:58,040
If that kid gets in,

248
00:12:58,840 --> 00:13:01,480
your niece can get in too.

249
00:13:02,740 --> 00:13:07,260
(Ningzhou County Qinqiang Opera Troupe)

250
00:13:08,680 --> 00:13:09,840
Many years later,

251
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:11,600
Hua Caixiang told Yi Qing'e

252
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,560
that her chance to perform in opera

253
00:13:13,920 --> 00:13:16,560
was bought with her uncle's blood.

254
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:26,520
Stop asking.

255
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:27,920
A donkey kicked me.

256
00:13:28,480 --> 00:13:29,440
Why are you here?

257
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:31,080
Waiting for the donkey.

258
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:33,000
Go inside.

259
00:13:39,160 --> 00:13:40,040
He Dachui did this?

260
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:41,440
Don't ask.

261
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:42,520
It's too embarrassing.

262
00:13:42,760 --> 00:13:43,600
Where's the kid?

263
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:44,600
Asleep.

264
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:48,880
He Dachui.

265
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:50,080
What happened?

266
00:13:50,280 --> 00:13:51,440
A donkey kicked me.

267
00:13:55,160 --> 00:13:56,000
Quick, quick.

268
00:13:56,240 --> 00:13:57,360
Wait, don't rush.

269
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:02,120
What kicked you?

270
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:04,040
Mind your own business.

271
00:14:04,040 --> 00:14:04,880
Your rook is gone.

272
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:08,720
Why did you steal my rook?

273
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:09,610
I didn't.

274
00:14:09,610 --> 00:14:10,460
Where's my rook?

275
00:14:10,460 --> 00:14:11,330
I haven't seen it.

276
00:14:11,330 --> 00:14:18,330
(County Troupe
New Trainee Audition Room)

277
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:22,540
Come on, come on.

278
00:14:22,540 --> 00:14:23,600
Make way, make way.

279
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:26,200
- How did it go?
- Come on, No. 20, step in.

280
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,300
- No. 20.
- Coming, coming.

281
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:29,040
Do your best.

282
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:32,680
Come on, this way.

283
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:34,400
Come here, let me take a look.

284
00:14:42,160 --> 00:14:44,560
Young man, step forward.

285
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,200
Center, center.

286
00:14:51,760 --> 00:14:52,800
More to the center.

287
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:54,600
Good, right, turn this way.

288
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:56,760
Give us a quick introduction.

289
00:14:57,320 --> 00:14:58,240
What's your name?

290
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:00,280
Heiwa.

291
00:15:01,040 --> 00:15:01,880
Louder.

292
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:05,720
I need to pee.

293
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:07,120
What?

294
00:15:07,379 --> 00:15:08,845
(Zhu Jiru, He Dachui)
I need to pee.

295
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:11,600
Go on, hurry up and go.

296
00:15:13,160 --> 00:15:14,000
Go.

297
00:15:21,440 --> 00:15:22,280
You have to learn.

298
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:23,960
I remember there were

299
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:26,560
two cans of canned mandarin oranges.

300
00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:28,050
Why?

301
00:15:28,050 --> 00:15:28,980
Let me borrow them.

302
00:15:30,100 --> 00:15:31,220
(Canned Mandarin Oranges)

303
00:15:31,220 --> 00:15:32,080
They really are here.

304
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:33,200
What do you need them for?

305
00:15:33,200 --> 00:15:34,200
It's urgent.

306
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:35,440
Go on, go on.

307
00:15:36,579 --> 00:15:37,882
When are you bringing them back?

308
00:15:37,960 --> 00:15:39,840
It's just two cans.

309
00:15:40,520 --> 00:15:41,760
Bring the net bag back to me.

310
00:15:42,560 --> 00:15:43,490
You little rascal.

311
00:15:43,490 --> 00:15:44,350
You need to pee?

312
00:15:44,350 --> 00:15:46,000
- I wanted to pee there.
- Not a drop.

313
00:15:46,360 --> 00:15:47,400
Don't scold him.

314
00:15:47,920 --> 00:15:49,360
You can't scold the kid now.

315
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:51,360
The more you scold, the tenser he gets.

316
00:15:51,880 --> 00:15:53,920
And then he can't pee at all.

317
00:15:53,920 --> 00:15:55,120
He needs to relax. Got it?

318
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:58,240
Look, look. Just relax.

319
00:15:59,300 --> 00:16:00,160
What are you doing?

320
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:01,000
I want to pee.

321
00:16:02,680 --> 00:16:03,520
He'll feel better.

322
00:16:04,480 --> 00:16:05,320
Who are you?

323
00:16:05,520 --> 00:16:06,600
I'm the lead drummer.

324
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:07,760
My name is Hu Sanyuan.

325
00:16:07,760 --> 00:16:09,880
Yinwa, when you were sick
a few days ago,

326
00:16:09,880 --> 00:16:11,600
I went to your place to check on you.

327
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:14,440
But Director Huang stopped me outside.

328
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:15,509
So, I never got to see you.

329
00:16:15,520 --> 00:16:16,720
Why wouldn't he let you in?

330
00:16:19,400 --> 00:16:20,840
I think Director Huang

331
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:22,600
was worried we'd join forces.

332
00:16:23,040 --> 00:16:23,880
What do you mean?

333
00:16:26,160 --> 00:16:27,620
This is your nephew, right?

334
00:16:27,620 --> 00:16:28,386
How did you know?

335
00:16:28,397 --> 00:16:29,670
He's trying out for the troupe?

336
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:32,780
Most likely, he won't make it.

337
00:16:32,980 --> 00:16:33,840
Who says that?

338
00:16:33,840 --> 00:16:34,680
I do.

339
00:16:41,280 --> 00:16:42,760
My niece is taking the test too.

340
00:16:43,580 --> 00:16:44,440
She knows nothing,

341
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:45,920
just like him.

342
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:48,040
What did Director Huang say?

343
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:49,400
Director Huang said

344
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:50,840
everyone's the same.

345
00:16:51,320 --> 00:16:52,600
No one gets special treatment.

346
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:56,520
Do you want the truth?

347
00:16:57,080 --> 00:16:57,920
Go on.

348
00:16:58,366 --> 00:16:59,360
How could it be the same?

349
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:00,960
Inside and outside aren't the same.

350
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:02,920
As far as I know,

351
00:17:02,920 --> 00:17:05,840
they're favoring
outside well-connected applicants.

352
00:17:06,600 --> 00:17:08,120
Kids from the troupe get sidelined.

353
00:17:08,680 --> 00:17:10,160
Director Huang told me

354
00:17:10,160 --> 00:17:11,120
it's up to their skills.

355
00:17:11,480 --> 00:17:12,880
That part is true enough,

356
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:14,560
but what even counts as skill?

357
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:17,080
Do you measure it or weigh it?

358
00:17:17,920 --> 00:17:20,080
Look at the Commerce Bureau,
Culture Bureau,

359
00:17:20,960 --> 00:17:22,040
and Materials Bureau.

360
00:17:22,360 --> 00:17:24,320
When the county does recruitment,

361
00:17:24,320 --> 00:17:26,040
don't they favor their own kids first?

362
00:17:26,360 --> 00:17:28,960
It's obvious he doesn't want
your nephew to get in.

363
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:32,880
I don't get
what Director Huang is thinking.

364
00:17:34,100 --> 00:17:36,006
Wouldn't it be better
to keep the kid close by?

365
00:17:37,040 --> 00:17:39,520
Director Huang said he has one vote.

366
00:17:40,040 --> 00:17:41,360
He alone can't decide

367
00:17:41,880 --> 00:17:43,200
who gets in.

368
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:44,600
That's true.

369
00:17:45,540 --> 00:17:46,400
Right now,

370
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:48,960
this is a rare chance
to change the kid's future.

371
00:17:49,520 --> 00:17:50,760
It hardly comes around in years.

372
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:52,840
Miss it, and it's gone for good.

373
00:17:52,840 --> 00:17:54,000
We can't let it slip by.

374
00:17:56,520 --> 00:17:57,640
So, what's your good idea?

375
00:17:58,080 --> 00:18:00,920
We need to stick together
and work as a team.

376
00:18:00,920 --> 00:18:02,960
We can't let outsiders get in.

377
00:18:03,760 --> 00:18:04,600
What do you mean?

378
00:18:05,520 --> 00:18:06,680
Five examiners in total.

379
00:18:08,760 --> 00:18:10,240
I can handle four.

380
00:18:11,440 --> 00:18:12,360
You can handle four?

381
00:18:12,360 --> 00:18:13,200
Of course.

382
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:14,040
What should I do?

383
00:18:14,240 --> 00:18:15,760
You take Director Huang.

384
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:19,240
Yinwa, in your family,

385
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:20,080
who calls the shots?

386
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:21,760
Obviously, I do.

387
00:18:22,280 --> 00:18:23,760
Then Director Huang is no problem.

388
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:25,880
Absolutely.

389
00:18:26,280 --> 00:18:27,120
It's settled.

390
00:18:29,760 --> 00:18:30,600
Your stuff.

391
00:18:42,080 --> 00:18:44,680
笙ｪThrough the forest笙ｪ

392
00:18:44,680 --> 00:18:48,480
笙ｪAcross the snowy plains笙ｪ

393
00:18:49,320 --> 00:18:50,440
笙ｪOur spirit soars笙ｪ

394
00:18:50,440 --> 00:18:53,960
笙ｪSetting free the hearts笙ｪ

395
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:57,200
First, no bragging. Second, stay calm.

396
00:18:57,200 --> 00:19:00,800
My grandpa met the Emperor.

397
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:04,360
My grandma dined with Her Highness.

398
00:19:04,360 --> 00:19:05,960
Calling it good means high praise.

399
00:19:05,960 --> 00:19:07,560
If it's so good that words fail you,

400
00:19:07,560 --> 00:19:09,200
you just say it's very good.

401
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:10,640
Very good. Very good.

402
00:19:11,040 --> 00:19:15,740
笙ｪHolding up a red lantern笙ｪ

403
00:19:16,220 --> 00:19:20,380
笙ｪLooking all around笙ｪ

404
00:19:27,060 --> 00:19:29,520
笙ｪSocialism is good, so very good笙ｪ

405
00:19:29,520 --> 00:19:30,840
Attention, please.

406
00:19:30,840 --> 00:19:32,920
Candidates and parents, take note.

407
00:19:32,920 --> 00:19:35,080
This morning's exam has ended.

408
00:19:35,080 --> 00:19:39,200
The next exam starts at 1 p.m.

409
00:19:39,960 --> 00:19:40,800
Attention, please.

410
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:42,960
Candidates and parents, take note.

411
00:19:43,233 --> 00:19:44,133
Director, you're back.

412
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:03,640
Why hide?

413
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:05,120
Come over and eat.

414
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:07,120
How did it go?

415
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:08,320
Have you given up now?

416
00:20:08,920 --> 00:20:10,920
You saw who came to test for us.

417
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:13,320
Every one of them is sharp.

418
00:20:14,160 --> 00:20:15,280
None of them is so foolish.

419
00:20:16,120 --> 00:20:17,080
Just send him back now.

420
00:20:17,600 --> 00:20:18,440
He can't go back.

421
00:20:18,680 --> 00:20:19,520
My brother said

422
00:20:19,840 --> 00:20:20,840
he wants us to adopt him.

423
00:20:21,440 --> 00:20:22,280
He's our kid now.

424
00:20:24,120 --> 00:20:25,760
Come on, this is absurd.

425
00:20:26,680 --> 00:20:27,960
Don't call him Uncle anymore.

426
00:20:27,960 --> 00:20:28,800
Call him Dad instead.

427
00:20:29,160 --> 00:20:30,280
Stop making a scene, okay?

428
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:32,520
Only vixens make a scene.

429
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:36,800
Fine, don't shout, okay?

430
00:20:38,040 --> 00:20:38,880
Yinwa,

431
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:41,160
please don't make this hard for me.

432
00:20:41,680 --> 00:20:43,840
The troupe is complicated.

433
00:20:44,180 --> 00:20:45,040
At this tryout,

434
00:20:45,040 --> 00:20:46,320
I'm not the only examiner.

435
00:20:46,320 --> 00:20:47,640
There are five examiners.

436
00:20:48,386 --> 00:20:50,040
How am I supposed
to tell the other four?

437
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:51,320
What should I say?

438
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:52,886
No need to talk to them.

439
00:20:53,280 --> 00:20:54,200
Someone else will.

440
00:20:56,040 --> 00:20:56,880
Who?

441
00:20:57,920 --> 00:20:59,320
The drummer from your troupe.

442
00:21:00,280 --> 00:21:01,200
His name's Hu Sanyuan.

443
00:21:03,280 --> 00:21:04,120
He came to see you?

444
00:21:13,040 --> 00:21:14,440
You got played again.

445
00:21:15,280 --> 00:21:16,120
What do you mean?

446
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:17,600
He used me for one vote,

447
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:18,760
and I used him for four votes.

448
00:21:19,280 --> 00:21:20,120
No way.

449
00:21:20,720 --> 00:21:22,560
You're such an idiot.

450
00:21:22,560 --> 00:21:23,840
You're the idiot here.

451
00:21:26,040 --> 00:21:26,880
Where are you going?

452
00:21:27,560 --> 00:21:28,400
Just eat.

453
00:21:37,320 --> 00:21:38,160
Director Huang.

454
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:03,840
Here.

455
00:22:04,120 --> 00:22:04,960
Chopsticks.

456
00:22:13,806 --> 00:22:14,880
The exam is this afternoon.

457
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:15,920
Don't eat so much.

458
00:22:16,960 --> 00:22:18,400
Why are the canned oranges back?

459
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:20,640
The job's done anyway.

460
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:22,240
Just keep them.

461
00:22:23,240 --> 00:22:24,320
Not one kid sang

462
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:25,640
Red Star this morning.

463
00:22:26,333 --> 00:22:27,739
She's the third one this afternoon.

464
00:22:28,146 --> 00:22:29,632
I hope the first two wouldn't sing it.

465
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:30,840
Why?

466
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:32,573
I don't want her compared to them.

467
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:38,440
Why not test who can eat the most?

468
00:22:39,280 --> 00:22:40,840
Our girl would pass that for sure.

469
00:22:41,280 --> 00:22:42,840
She can eat eight Mo in one meal.

470
00:22:50,360 --> 00:22:53,560
Singing isn't that hard, okay?

471
00:22:54,480 --> 00:22:57,160
You just need to start the first line

472
00:22:57,760 --> 00:22:58,600
and sing it out loud.

473
00:23:00,440 --> 00:23:02,640
I'm talking to you.
Where are you looking at?

474
00:23:04,280 --> 00:23:05,320
Open your mouth.

475
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:07,280
Sing with confidence.

476
00:23:08,560 --> 00:23:10,510
Sing it as Aunt Hua taught you, okay?

477
00:23:10,510 --> 00:23:11,760
No. 40, come on in.

478
00:23:11,760 --> 00:23:12,600
No. 40.

479
00:23:13,480 --> 00:23:14,360
Come, this way.

480
00:23:14,360 --> 00:23:15,329
Easy, easy.

481
00:23:15,340 --> 00:23:16,280
Give me the form. Okay.

482
00:23:16,280 --> 00:23:18,280
Hello, everyone. I'm Feng Xiaoxiao.

483
00:23:18,280 --> 00:23:20,720
I'm 13 this year and love the arts.

484
00:23:20,720 --> 00:23:22,640
I like singing and performing in opera.

485
00:23:22,640 --> 00:23:24,080
I can also play the accordion.

486
00:23:24,080 --> 00:23:26,440
Next, I'll sing Red Star
while accompanying myself.

487
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:27,760
Please judge.

488
00:23:29,120 --> 00:23:32,720
笙ｪThe red star is twinkling笙ｪ

489
00:23:33,080 --> 00:23:36,800
笙ｪThe red star warms our hearts笙ｪ

490
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:37,680
The red star is...

491
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:38,640
Hold on. Hold on.

492
00:23:41,120 --> 00:23:41,960
Hua Caixiang,

493
00:23:42,440 --> 00:23:43,960
why did you stop him like that?

494
00:23:44,080 --> 00:23:46,200
I don't think applicants can use backup.

495
00:23:46,640 --> 00:23:47,480
Why not?

496
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:48,440
Well...

497
00:23:48,680 --> 00:23:49,960
With backing music,

498
00:23:49,960 --> 00:23:51,566
how can you judge the sound,

499
00:23:51,577 --> 00:23:52,560
pitch, and tone quality?

500
00:23:52,560 --> 00:23:53,593
What are you listening to?

501
00:23:54,880 --> 00:23:56,240
Hua Caixiang has a point.

502
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:58,880
Kid, can you sing without this?

503
00:23:58,880 --> 00:24:00,320
Okay, sir.

504
00:24:00,320 --> 00:24:01,280
Just sing.

505
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:12,400
笙ｪThe red star is twinkling笙ｪ

506
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:16,240
笙ｪThe red star warms our hearts笙ｪ

507
00:24:16,240 --> 00:24:19,880
笙ｪThe red star is the heart
of the workers and peasants笙ｪ

508
00:24:19,880 --> 00:24:23,880
笙ｪThe Party's glory shines
for generations笙ｪ

509
00:24:23,880 --> 00:24:27,760
笙ｪThe red star is the heart
of the workers and peasants笙ｪ

510
00:24:27,760 --> 00:24:31,200
笙ｪThe Party's glory shines
for generations笙ｪ

511
00:24:31,760 --> 00:24:32,800
Come on, make some room.

512
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:35,680
Whose child is this? Come down.

513
00:24:35,740 --> 00:24:36,600
No. 41.

514
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:38,060
- Here, here.
- No. 41.

515
00:24:38,060 --> 00:24:38,920
Here.

516
00:24:38,920 --> 00:24:39,840
Hand me the form.

517
00:24:43,760 --> 00:24:44,600
What is it, bro?

518
00:24:46,240 --> 00:24:47,080
Move aside.

519
00:24:56,280 --> 00:24:57,680
Stand in the middle.

520
00:24:58,680 --> 00:24:59,520
Come here.

521
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:03,960
Introduce yourself first.

522
00:25:04,320 --> 00:25:06,000
What's your name and your age?

523
00:25:15,600 --> 00:25:16,880
Don't be nervous.

524
00:25:17,920 --> 00:25:19,120
Speak up.

525
00:25:19,840 --> 00:25:22,280
Yi Qing'e, 11 years old.

526
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:24,640
Why don't you come in and try?

527
00:25:27,520 --> 00:25:28,600
Let her try.

528
00:25:29,480 --> 00:25:30,320
Yi Qing'e.

529
00:25:30,440 --> 00:25:31,360
Now, perform the piece

530
00:25:31,360 --> 00:25:32,400
you prepared.

531
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:34,800
If you can't sing, dance instead.

532
00:25:35,760 --> 00:25:36,600
Yi Qing'e.

533
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:39,320
Don't be nervous.

534
00:25:40,360 --> 00:25:42,200
Just do it the way

535
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:43,240
Ms. Hua taught you.

536
00:25:49,840 --> 00:25:53,840
笙ｪThe red star is twinkling笙ｪ

537
00:25:53,840 --> 00:25:54,960
Shut that mouth of yours.

538
00:25:56,320 --> 00:25:57,940
The kid who just came in set the key

539
00:25:57,940 --> 00:25:58,790
with an accordion.

540
00:25:58,790 --> 00:26:00,360
Then I'll set the key with my voice.

541
00:26:00,680 --> 00:26:02,840
Hu Sanyuan, this is my exam room.

542
00:26:02,840 --> 00:26:03,960
Stop fooling around.

543
00:26:07,040 --> 00:26:07,880
Sing.

544
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:09,400
Sing louder.

545
00:26:10,040 --> 00:26:11,920
Don't let them think you're mute.

546
00:26:13,460 --> 00:26:14,320
Dad.

547
00:26:14,320 --> 00:26:15,166
I'll switch with her.

548
00:26:15,177 --> 00:26:16,595
Let her marry the team leader's son.

549
00:26:16,606 --> 00:26:17,840
Dad doesn't want me anymore.

550
00:26:17,840 --> 00:26:19,440
Your mom just got you a little brother.

551
00:26:19,440 --> 00:26:20,640
It's harder to feed you all.

552
00:26:20,640 --> 00:26:22,360
If she fails, don't let her back.

553
00:26:22,640 --> 00:26:23,953
How can you be so disappointing?

554
00:26:23,964 --> 00:26:24,928
Forget about your uncle.

555
00:26:24,939 --> 00:26:25,920
I'm getting anxious too.

556
00:26:25,920 --> 00:26:26,840
If you leave with me,

557
00:26:26,840 --> 00:26:27,800
there's no turning back.

558
00:26:27,800 --> 00:26:29,040
Just sing up front.

559
00:26:29,040 --> 00:26:30,920
Let's win this one together.

560
00:26:30,920 --> 00:26:31,800
Sing.

561
00:26:32,760 --> 00:26:37,080
笙ｪOnce outside, my back feels behind笙ｪ

562
00:26:37,080 --> 00:26:41,400
笙ｪSo I can keep my belly out front笙ｪ

563
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:45,720
笙ｪAll uncles are uncles笙ｪ

564
00:26:45,720 --> 00:26:49,760
笙ｪTables and stools are all wood笙ｪ

565
00:26:50,200 --> 00:26:54,240
笙ｪOne step forward and one step back
means nothing笙ｪ

566
00:26:54,240 --> 00:26:58,080
笙ｪDonkeys and oxen are beasts笙ｪ

567
00:26:58,080 --> 00:27:02,040
笙ｪGold and silver aren't enough笙ｪ

568
00:27:02,040 --> 00:27:05,920
笙ｪHeaven above and earth below,
kid, don't get cocky笙ｪ

569
00:27:06,520 --> 00:27:10,440
笙ｪAll the uncles are beasts笙ｪ

570
00:27:10,440 --> 00:27:13,680
笙ｪPigs, horses, cows, and sheep
are all your uncles笙ｪ

571
00:27:13,960 --> 00:27:15,360
(That shepherd girl's cry)

572
00:27:15,360 --> 00:27:17,000
(was finally forced out of her.)

573
00:27:17,080 --> 00:27:19,320
(If she didn't shout,
she'd choke on it.)

574
00:27:19,640 --> 00:27:21,720
(She felt wronged. She couldn't get it.)

575
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:23,080
(Why perform in opera?)

576
00:27:23,200 --> 00:27:25,360
(Why does she have to listen to them?)

577
00:27:26,000 --> 00:27:28,040
(That cry was her protest.)

578
00:27:28,320 --> 00:27:29,840
(She wanted her uncle to give up.)

579
00:27:30,320 --> 00:27:31,680
(But once she opened her voice,)

580
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:33,900
(she just couldn't stop anymore.)

581
00:27:33,900 --> 00:27:34,760
Stop.

582
00:27:34,760 --> 00:27:35,933
(Qinqiang Opera Troupe)
Stop.

583
00:27:36,360 --> 00:27:37,200
Okay.

584
00:27:37,280 --> 00:27:38,160
What are you doing?

585
00:27:38,280 --> 00:27:39,120
Gou.

586
00:27:39,640 --> 00:27:40,640
Qiu Cunyi's guest.

587
00:27:40,920 --> 00:27:41,760
Register them.

588
00:27:42,040 --> 00:27:43,240
Go ahead.

589
00:27:46,360 --> 00:27:47,880
What play is this?

590
00:27:47,880 --> 00:27:48,800
Ye Zhu Lin.

591
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:52,760
Where did you go?

592
00:27:54,320 --> 00:27:55,400
He Dachui's hometown.

593
00:27:56,760 --> 00:27:59,120
You two are really that close now?

594
00:27:59,760 --> 00:28:00,630
No kidding.

595
00:28:00,630 --> 00:28:02,520
He Dachui can be pretty loyal sometimes.

596
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:05,760
Then your pant leg must be really wide.

597
00:28:05,920 --> 00:28:07,320
Whoever shows you loyalty,

598
00:28:07,320 --> 00:28:08,760
you'll share your pant leg with them.

599
00:28:08,760 --> 00:28:10,440
That sounds pretty harsh.

600
00:28:12,320 --> 00:28:14,160
They'll make the decision
at the meeting soon.

601
00:28:14,160 --> 00:28:15,440
Aren't you worried?

602
00:28:38,160 --> 00:28:41,320
We're taking in 30 trainees in total.

603
00:28:41,480 --> 00:28:42,720
18 boys

604
00:28:42,920 --> 00:28:43,800
and 12 girls.

605
00:28:44,840 --> 00:28:48,760
Based on the examiners' scores,

606
00:28:48,760 --> 00:28:50,840
we need to confirm

607
00:28:50,840 --> 00:28:52,040
the final list today.

608
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:54,280
Let's have Director Huang

609
00:28:54,280 --> 00:28:55,680
set the tone for us first.

610
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:03,800
As for this shortlist,

611
00:29:04,280 --> 00:29:06,760
I have no issue

612
00:29:07,080 --> 00:29:08,080
with 28 of the top 30.

613
00:29:09,840 --> 00:29:11,040
There are only two people

614
00:29:11,640 --> 00:29:12,960
I just can't make sense of.

615
00:29:15,280 --> 00:29:16,160
First,

616
00:29:16,440 --> 00:29:17,520
Zhang Heiwa.

617
00:29:18,200 --> 00:29:19,440
You all know

618
00:29:19,440 --> 00:29:21,440
this kid is my wife's nephew.

619
00:29:21,440 --> 00:29:23,280
I've said it again and again:

620
00:29:23,280 --> 00:29:24,840
Don't pull any shady stuff.

621
00:29:25,400 --> 00:29:26,320
So, tell me.

622
00:29:26,320 --> 00:29:28,000
This kid can barely put words together.

623
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:30,080
How did he still get 95?

624
00:29:30,080 --> 00:29:30,920
Such a high score.

625
00:29:32,280 --> 00:29:33,120
Everyone,

626
00:29:33,800 --> 00:29:35,560
I want to hear your reasons.

627
00:29:44,800 --> 00:29:46,640
Now that we're talking,

628
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:48,280
can someone say something?

629
00:29:52,600 --> 00:29:54,040
Then I'll go first.

630
00:29:54,560 --> 00:29:55,680
Look at our troupe.

631
00:29:56,400 --> 00:29:57,520
This tryout

632
00:29:58,160 --> 00:30:00,160
isn't just for the future lead.

633
00:30:00,600 --> 00:30:01,920
More importantly,

634
00:30:02,680 --> 00:30:05,050
we need supporting actors and extras.

635
00:30:05,050 --> 00:30:05,900
Exactly.

636
00:30:05,900 --> 00:30:06,740
- Right?
- Yes.

637
00:30:06,920 --> 00:30:07,810
- Right.
- If we

638
00:30:07,810 --> 00:30:10,280
cast everyone by the lead's bar,

639
00:30:10,881 --> 00:30:12,115
who'll be the supporting actor?

640
00:30:12,126 --> 00:30:12,900
Exactly.

641
00:30:12,950 --> 00:30:15,800
Who'd gladly prop up the lead?

642
00:30:15,800 --> 00:30:16,640
Look.

643
00:30:17,040 --> 00:30:19,160
Zhang Heiwa is a countryside boy,

644
00:30:19,160 --> 00:30:20,000
plain and honest.

645
00:30:20,240 --> 00:30:21,600
When he was taking the test,

646
00:30:21,920 --> 00:30:23,720
when he had to go, he just went.

647
00:30:23,720 --> 00:30:25,400
Right, he didn't hold it back.

648
00:30:25,840 --> 00:30:27,320
Most importantly,

649
00:30:27,320 --> 00:30:30,200
this kid naturally carries

650
00:30:30,200 --> 00:30:31,920
the air of poor
and lower-middle peasants.

651
00:30:32,600 --> 00:30:34,320
That's exactly what our troupe needs.

652
00:30:35,240 --> 00:30:36,253
That's all I have to say.

653
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:40,600
I fully agree with Deputy Director Zhu.

654
00:30:40,920 --> 00:30:42,200
That's exactly how I see it too.

655
00:30:42,720 --> 00:30:46,200
Director Huang stressed many times

656
00:30:46,200 --> 00:30:48,520
that we'd rather take poor
and lower-middle peasants

657
00:30:48,920 --> 00:30:50,600
than the seedlings of the bourgeoisie.

658
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:54,960
This kid is the greenest grass around.

659
00:30:55,600 --> 00:30:56,440
If not him, then who?

660
00:30:56,640 --> 00:30:57,750
- Right.
- Right?

661
00:30:57,750 --> 00:30:58,600
Right.

662
00:31:00,800 --> 00:31:01,640
Here, here.

663
00:31:02,560 --> 00:31:03,400
Grab its ears.

664
00:31:08,560 --> 00:31:09,800
All of you can't catch one pig?

665
00:31:09,800 --> 00:31:10,840
What are you doing?

666
00:31:11,200 --> 00:31:12,280
Where'd this pig come from?

667
00:31:12,560 --> 00:31:14,080
Hu Sanyuan bought a pig.

668
00:31:14,080 --> 00:31:16,120
Tonight, he's treating the troupe
to braised pork.

669
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:17,720
Take it to the front yard.

670
00:31:17,720 --> 00:31:19,280
We're in an important meeting. Move.

671
00:31:24,160 --> 00:31:25,240
Back in our village,

672
00:31:25,760 --> 00:31:28,160
half a pig could get you a wife.

673
00:31:28,800 --> 00:31:30,200
Your uncle is so generous.

674
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:31,840
For your sake,

675
00:31:32,280 --> 00:31:34,160
he gave away two wives' worth of meat.

676
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:37,000
You'd better try your best.

677
00:31:37,560 --> 00:31:39,120
Otherwise, that pig died for nothing.

678
00:31:40,440 --> 00:31:42,160
That pig didn't die for me.

679
00:31:42,880 --> 00:31:44,600
When pigs grow up, they get eaten.

680
00:31:45,280 --> 00:31:46,320
That's just its fate.

681
00:31:51,720 --> 00:31:52,920
If my dad hadn't been there,

682
00:31:53,200 --> 00:31:54,640
I'd have dropped that pig flat.

683
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:58,000
Who are you dropping?

684
00:32:00,120 --> 00:32:01,040
You've made it for me?

685
00:32:01,400 --> 00:32:02,240
Let me see.

686
00:32:04,520 --> 00:32:05,760
You little brat.

687
00:32:06,400 --> 00:32:07,240
Give it to me.

688
00:32:10,320 --> 00:32:11,160
Give it to me.

689
00:32:14,360 --> 00:32:15,240
Let go.

690
00:32:17,080 --> 00:32:18,760
Getting bold now?

691
00:32:33,760 --> 00:32:35,440
Now, about the girls,

692
00:32:37,120 --> 00:32:39,320
Chu Jiahe is No. 1.

693
00:32:40,080 --> 00:32:40,960
I'm okay with that.

694
00:32:41,520 --> 00:32:43,320
Her strengths are obvious.

695
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:45,840
As for Yi Qing'e,

696
00:32:46,360 --> 00:32:48,440
you can't get a word out of her.

697
00:32:49,040 --> 00:32:51,040
How did she get 97?

698
00:32:51,520 --> 00:32:52,760
She's even placed second.

699
00:32:53,520 --> 00:32:54,440
Come on, come on.

700
00:32:54,440 --> 00:32:55,480
Let's hear your thoughts.

701
00:32:56,840 --> 00:32:57,800
What's your reason?

702
00:32:59,400 --> 00:33:00,240
Director,

703
00:33:01,400 --> 00:33:02,840
why do you keep looking outside?

704
00:33:03,400 --> 00:33:04,600
The pig had run off.

705
00:33:05,400 --> 00:33:06,240
Say a few words.

706
00:33:08,960 --> 00:33:10,840
Then I'll share my view.

707
00:33:12,280 --> 00:33:13,560
As for Yi Qing'e,

708
00:33:14,560 --> 00:33:16,400
those few lines she belted that day show

709
00:33:16,880 --> 00:33:19,800
she has a wide range and strong reach.

710
00:33:19,800 --> 00:33:20,940
- Yes.
- It's very moving.

711
00:33:20,940 --> 00:33:21,780
Yes.

712
00:33:21,780 --> 00:33:22,620
And one more thing.

713
00:33:22,880 --> 00:33:23,960
I think this is important.

714
00:33:24,360 --> 00:33:25,520
I noticed this kid has

715
00:33:25,520 --> 00:33:26,920
really strong mental composure.

716
00:33:27,760 --> 00:33:29,170
That day, she played the scarecrow.

717
00:33:29,170 --> 00:33:30,040
Right.

718
00:33:30,040 --> 00:33:31,326
That was her first time on stage.

719
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:33,560
Her very first performance ever.

720
00:33:33,560 --> 00:33:34,420
Right.

721
00:33:34,420 --> 00:33:37,000
I didn't see a hint of fear in her.

722
00:33:37,960 --> 00:33:40,240
Director Huang praised her a lot too

723
00:33:40,240 --> 00:33:41,480
and told us to promote her hard.

724
00:33:41,480 --> 00:33:42,393
Right, Director Huang?

725
00:33:42,700 --> 00:33:43,660
Right, right.

726
00:33:43,660 --> 00:33:44,520
So,

727
00:33:44,520 --> 00:33:46,040
mental toughness

728
00:33:46,040 --> 00:33:48,880
is incredibly important

729
00:33:49,280 --> 00:33:50,140
for someone in acting.

730
00:33:50,140 --> 00:33:51,000
Well said, Director.

731
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:52,680
I really think Director is spot-on.

732
00:33:53,040 --> 00:33:55,000
This kid is gutsy.

733
00:33:55,560 --> 00:33:56,800
She'd even catch snakes.

734
00:33:57,440 --> 00:33:59,520
There were often snakes in rehearsal.

735
00:33:59,520 --> 00:34:00,640
I'm terrified of snakes.

736
00:34:00,960 --> 00:34:02,240
With her in rehearsal,

737
00:34:02,240 --> 00:34:03,560
I can finally relax.

738
00:34:03,560 --> 00:34:04,400
Mi Lan,

739
00:34:05,280 --> 00:34:06,473
what kind of reason is that?

740
00:34:06,800 --> 00:34:07,800
Am I recruiting trainees

741
00:34:07,800 --> 00:34:08,960
or finding you a bodyguard?

742
00:34:09,920 --> 00:34:10,760
Hold it together.

743
00:34:19,120 --> 00:34:20,800
Director, didn't you notice this?

744
00:34:20,800 --> 00:34:22,000
Yi Qing'e

745
00:34:22,560 --> 00:34:23,720
is like Changbao

746
00:34:23,720 --> 00:34:25,960
in Zhi Qu Wei Hu Shan,

747
00:34:26,600 --> 00:34:28,560
Li Tiemei in Hong Deng Ji,

748
00:34:28,560 --> 00:34:30,480
and Jiang Shuiying in Long Jiang Song.

749
00:34:31,120 --> 00:34:32,200
How did you see that?

750
00:34:32,920 --> 00:34:34,000
Once she stands there,

751
00:34:34,000 --> 00:34:36,560
she has that bold, righteous spirit,

752
00:34:36,960 --> 00:34:38,400
not drawn to glamour, but to duty.

753
00:34:38,400 --> 00:34:39,840
That fearless presence.

754
00:34:39,840 --> 00:34:41,200
Once she starts performing, look.

755
00:34:41,200 --> 00:34:42,040
Right, right.

756
00:34:42,393 --> 00:34:44,200
Why not say she's like Grandma Li,
Aunt Qing,

757
00:34:44,200 --> 00:34:45,213
or the White-Haired Girl?

758
00:34:45,600 --> 00:34:47,400
She's too young for Grandma Li.

759
00:34:50,240 --> 00:34:51,400
Why laugh? Keep it together.

760
00:34:51,960 --> 00:34:52,800
Keep what together?

761
00:34:53,040 --> 00:34:54,040
Just speak your mind.

762
00:34:58,880 --> 00:34:59,840
Then I'll say

763
00:35:00,680 --> 00:35:01,560
something.

764
00:35:02,240 --> 00:35:05,160
As for Zhang Heiwa and Yi Qing'e,

765
00:35:05,720 --> 00:35:07,320
these two kids

766
00:35:07,880 --> 00:35:10,280
both carry that air

767
00:35:10,280 --> 00:35:11,840
of poor and lower-middle peasants.

768
00:35:12,600 --> 00:35:14,400
The key point is

769
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:16,760
that they're both the greenest grass

770
00:35:17,520 --> 00:35:19,680
from our troupe.

771
00:35:22,240 --> 00:35:23,520
When I said that back then,

772
00:35:23,520 --> 00:35:25,200
there was a specific context.

773
00:35:27,360 --> 00:35:28,720
Country bumpkins make trouble

774
00:35:29,080 --> 00:35:30,600
in the troupe?

775
00:35:31,080 --> 00:35:32,120
Is there no order left?

776
00:35:32,480 --> 00:35:33,400
Where's justice?

777
00:35:33,560 --> 00:35:34,840
What's wrong? I'm in a meeting.

778
00:35:34,840 --> 00:35:36,400
Director Huang, the kid from outside

779
00:35:36,400 --> 00:35:37,770
smashed my kid's head open.

780
00:35:37,770 --> 00:35:38,790
- What happened?
- Look.

781
00:35:38,790 --> 00:35:39,640
Look, look.

782
00:35:39,640 --> 00:35:40,750
What is it? Who did it?

783
00:35:40,750 --> 00:35:41,816
- Who did it?
- He's hurt.

784
00:35:42,440 --> 00:35:43,680
That outsider kid did it.

785
00:35:43,680 --> 00:35:45,400
Er Laizi hit me first.

786
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:46,920
He slapped me several times.

787
00:35:47,240 --> 00:35:48,360
Then Laidi hit him.

788
00:35:48,360 --> 00:35:50,120
I hit you, not her.

789
00:35:51,520 --> 00:35:52,360
How fierce.

790
00:35:52,680 --> 00:35:54,760
You really have no sense at all.

791
00:35:54,760 --> 00:35:55,880
If you're picking a fight,

792
00:35:56,160 --> 00:35:57,680
why pick the bigger one

793
00:35:57,900 --> 00:35:58,760
and a boy at that?

794
00:35:58,760 --> 00:36:00,686
You even hit the Head
of Security Section's kid.

795
00:36:01,280 --> 00:36:02,920
Hu Sanyuan, what do you mean?

796
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:05,280
You can't even understand plain words?

797
00:36:05,280 --> 00:36:06,360
What do you think I mean?

798
00:36:07,440 --> 00:36:08,640
I mean, he had it coming.

799
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:11,120
You little brat.

800
00:36:11,280 --> 00:36:12,520
You never do anything right,

801
00:36:12,520 --> 00:36:14,080
always with a cigarette and that cap on.

802
00:36:14,080 --> 00:36:15,530
Don't your parents care?

803
00:36:15,530 --> 00:36:16,430
You even hit my kid.

804
00:36:16,430 --> 00:36:17,280
I didn't hit him.

805
00:36:17,280 --> 00:36:18,150
You shut your mouth.

806
00:36:18,150 --> 00:36:19,000
- Guo.
- Here.

807
00:36:19,200 --> 00:36:20,460
- Take them back.
- Yes.

808
00:36:20,640 --> 00:36:22,233
We're in a meeting. Quit making a scene.

809
00:36:22,520 --> 00:36:23,360
Come on, move.

810
00:36:23,640 --> 00:36:24,480
Go.

811
00:36:24,573 --> 00:36:26,400
I told you to watch the kid.
What did you do?

812
00:36:26,400 --> 00:36:27,520
You need a lesson.

813
00:36:28,600 --> 00:36:29,500
Don't hit him.

814
00:36:29,500 --> 00:36:30,360
Let's go home.

815
00:36:30,360 --> 00:36:31,880
Alright, get back now.

816
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:33,280
Why come here?

817
00:36:33,560 --> 00:36:34,586
He was picking on the kid.

818
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:35,960
We were in a meeting.

819
00:36:41,240 --> 00:36:42,160
You're quite bold.

820
00:36:45,280 --> 00:36:46,280
She praised you.

821
00:36:49,680 --> 00:36:50,520
Look.

822
00:36:51,440 --> 00:36:52,280
How many?

823
00:36:52,760 --> 00:36:53,600
One.

824
00:36:54,120 --> 00:36:54,960
Three.

825
00:36:55,440 --> 00:36:56,280
You're not blind.

826
00:36:57,400 --> 00:36:59,080
You saw wrong and stepped in.

827
00:36:59,080 --> 00:37:01,120
But what did that have to do with you?

828
00:37:01,640 --> 00:37:02,760
You could've fought anytime,

829
00:37:02,760 --> 00:37:03,880
but you fought right in front

830
00:37:03,880 --> 00:37:06,680
of Huang Zhengjing and the examiners?

831
00:37:06,680 --> 00:37:07,760
That swing of yours

832
00:37:07,760 --> 00:37:08,680
made your uncle's pig

833
00:37:09,040 --> 00:37:09,880
go to waste.

834
00:37:19,040 --> 00:37:19,880
Sanyuan.

835
00:37:19,980 --> 00:37:20,840
Hi.

836
00:37:20,840 --> 00:37:21,680
Hello.

837
00:37:30,920 --> 00:37:32,000
Yinwa, you're here.

838
00:37:33,400 --> 00:37:34,240
What brings you here?

839
00:37:34,720 --> 00:37:35,640
What are you up to?

840
00:37:35,640 --> 00:37:36,920
The cafeteria butchered a pig.

841
00:37:37,200 --> 00:37:39,400
We saved the head for you
and Director Huang.

842
00:37:39,400 --> 00:37:40,360
That doesn't seem right.

843
00:37:40,840 --> 00:37:41,680
It's totally fine.

844
00:37:42,200 --> 00:37:44,320
Chef Song only knows canteen stew.

845
00:37:44,640 --> 00:37:46,040
If he handles this pig head,

846
00:37:46,040 --> 00:37:46,880
it'll go to waste.

847
00:37:47,020 --> 00:37:47,880
That's exactly right.

848
00:37:47,880 --> 00:37:49,200
Most people can't deal with this.

849
00:37:49,200 --> 00:37:50,080
It's a real hassle.

850
00:37:50,213 --> 00:37:51,140
Where should I put it?

851
00:37:51,140 --> 00:37:51,980
Come on.

852
00:37:51,980 --> 00:37:52,820
Put it right here.

853
00:37:55,520 --> 00:37:56,360
Here, here.

854
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:57,840
Have a seat.

855
00:37:57,940 --> 00:37:58,800
Right, right.

856
00:37:58,800 --> 00:38:00,240
This is fine. I can handle it.

857
00:38:00,240 --> 00:38:01,560
Have some water. Pour it yourself.

858
00:38:01,560 --> 00:38:02,920
My hands are really dirty.

859
00:38:02,920 --> 00:38:03,760
Come here.

860
00:38:04,080 --> 00:38:05,760
Thank Grandma for speaking up for you.

861
00:38:07,080 --> 00:38:08,760
We're peers,

862
00:38:09,120 --> 00:38:10,480
and she calls me Grandma?

863
00:38:10,480 --> 00:38:11,320
Call me Aunt.

864
00:38:11,880 --> 00:38:13,800
Right, thank Aunt.

865
00:38:15,880 --> 00:38:17,960
This kid's shy. She doesn't talk much.

866
00:38:18,640 --> 00:38:19,600
Shy?

867
00:38:19,880 --> 00:38:20,920
She got quite a backbone.

868
00:38:21,240 --> 00:38:22,800
Now, someone can handle that bad kid.

869
00:38:24,040 --> 00:38:26,280
Director Huang and the others
are in a meeting.

870
00:38:26,960 --> 00:38:29,320
They're deciding these two kids' future.

871
00:38:32,960 --> 00:38:34,000
Tell me the truth.

872
00:38:34,600 --> 00:38:36,120
Was what the anonymous letter said

873
00:38:36,480 --> 00:38:37,520
real or not?

874
00:38:38,086 --> 00:38:39,080
It's hard for me to say.

875
00:38:39,080 --> 00:38:40,040
I can't talk carelessly.

876
00:38:40,320 --> 00:38:41,160
What's wrong?

877
00:38:41,440 --> 00:38:42,360
You still treat me

878
00:38:42,760 --> 00:38:43,920
like an outsider now?

879
00:38:45,880 --> 00:38:47,200
I do have a suggestion.

880
00:38:48,160 --> 00:38:49,000
Go on.

881
00:38:52,360 --> 00:38:55,480
If you stay with the troupe,

882
00:38:56,080 --> 00:38:57,480
it'll be like giving Director Huang

883
00:38:57,480 --> 00:38:59,240
a layer of protection, you know?

884
00:38:59,640 --> 00:39:01,960
You'll block the sugar-coated bullets

885
00:39:01,960 --> 00:39:03,600
and the overt and covert attacks.

886
00:39:04,640 --> 00:39:05,480
Exactly.

887
00:39:05,693 --> 00:39:06,920
That's what I was thinking too.

888
00:39:08,840 --> 00:39:09,840
I caught the smell.

889
00:39:14,520 --> 00:39:15,380
Quick.

890
00:39:15,380 --> 00:39:16,240
Don't climb up.

891
00:39:16,240 --> 00:39:17,280
Hurry, get back.

892
00:39:17,280 --> 00:39:18,280
Everyone will get it.

893
00:39:18,380 --> 00:39:19,270
You cut in line again.

894
00:39:19,270 --> 00:39:20,560
Keep the kid down there.

895
00:39:20,560 --> 00:39:21,600
Don't let the kid fall.

896
00:39:21,600 --> 00:39:22,440
So what?

897
00:39:23,440 --> 00:39:24,280
I'm cutting the line.

898
00:39:24,720 --> 00:39:25,560
I'm telling you.

899
00:39:25,960 --> 00:39:27,720
Without me, none of you'd get pork.

900
00:39:29,160 --> 00:39:30,000
Alright, alright.

901
00:39:30,720 --> 00:39:33,040
Hu Sanyuan and I hauled that pig back.

902
00:39:33,560 --> 00:39:35,360
At first,
it wouldn't get on the tractor.

903
00:39:35,800 --> 00:39:37,000
I had a heart-to-heart with it.

904
00:39:39,760 --> 00:39:40,840
What did you say?

905
00:39:40,840 --> 00:39:41,680
Listen to me.

906
00:39:41,920 --> 00:39:42,920
I told the pig

907
00:39:42,920 --> 00:39:45,120
that Hu Sanyuan invited you here.

908
00:39:45,760 --> 00:39:47,240
You can ignore me if you want,

909
00:39:47,760 --> 00:39:49,760
but you dare ignore Hu Sanyuan?

910
00:39:51,720 --> 00:39:53,379
It doesn't matter
that you're just a pig.

911
00:39:53,680 --> 00:39:55,720
Even the Director would have to go.

912
00:39:57,860 --> 00:39:58,720
I'm telling you.

913
00:39:58,720 --> 00:40:00,800
The second it heard that, it jumped

914
00:40:01,360 --> 00:40:02,440
right onto the tractor.

915
00:40:04,373 --> 00:40:05,526
Shouldn't you be thanking me?

916
00:40:05,700 --> 00:40:06,560
You owe me this.

917
00:40:06,560 --> 00:40:08,920
Hu Sanyuan really carries weight.

918
00:40:11,280 --> 00:40:15,880
That big hog listens to him the most.

919
00:40:17,360 --> 00:40:18,280
This pork is delicious.

920
00:40:19,480 --> 00:40:20,320
Eat a little more.

921
00:40:30,320 --> 00:40:31,680
Why is your bowl packed with meat?

922
00:40:32,640 --> 00:40:34,560
I got that whole pig brought back.

923
00:40:34,560 --> 00:40:35,640
So what if I eat more?

924
00:40:37,080 --> 00:40:38,040
Don't sit over here.

925
00:40:38,400 --> 00:40:39,240
Why not?

926
00:40:39,800 --> 00:40:40,760
Watch how this looks.

927
00:40:41,440 --> 00:40:42,480
Since when do you care?

928
00:40:44,920 --> 00:40:45,920
Fine, fine. Sit here.

929
00:40:45,920 --> 00:40:46,760
Here, sit here.

930
00:40:47,400 --> 00:40:48,280
Where are you going?

931
00:40:48,720 --> 00:40:49,560
Come back.

932
00:40:51,760 --> 00:40:55,240
Hu Sanyuan really carries weight.

933
00:40:55,240 --> 00:40:58,720
That big hog listens to him the most.

934
00:40:59,120 --> 00:41:00,640
Stop egging it on over there.

935
00:41:03,200 --> 00:41:04,040
Hi, Director Huang.

936
00:42:12,540 --> 00:42:16,100
笙ｪSocialism is good, so very good笙ｪ

937
00:42:16,100 --> 00:42:20,020
笙ｪIn a socialist state,
people stand tall笙ｪ

938
00:42:20,020 --> 00:42:21,940
笙ｪThe hostile forces are brought down笙ｪ

939
00:42:21,940 --> 00:42:25,380
笙ｪThe imperialists ran off in defeat笙ｪ

940
00:42:26,060 --> 00:42:28,020
笙ｪAll our people stand united as one笙ｪ

941
00:42:28,020 --> 00:42:28,940
(Boys)

942
00:42:28,940 --> 00:42:29,910
(Li Jianguo, Guo Zhiyong)

943
00:42:30,050 --> 00:42:31,300
(Feng Xiaoxiao, Ma Weiqiang)

944
00:42:31,300 --> 00:42:33,020
(Zhang Heiwa, Feng Hongzhi,
Zhao Shengli)

945
00:42:33,300 --> 00:42:34,980
笙ｪA wave of socialist building笙ｪ

946
00:42:34,980 --> 00:42:36,080
(Girls)

947
00:42:36,091 --> 00:42:37,380
(Chu Jiahe, Yu Liping, Yi Qing'e)

948
00:42:37,380 --> 00:42:39,870
(Chen Hongjuan, Lin Hongmei,
Liu Hongling, Zhou Yuzhi)

949
00:42:39,870 --> 00:42:40,780
笙ｪThe Party笙ｪ

950
00:42:49,480 --> 00:42:50,560
How is it? Happy now?

951
00:42:51,000 --> 00:42:51,880
Yeah.

952
00:42:59,020 --> 00:43:04,940
(Department Store)

953
00:43:05,020 --> 00:43:06,940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

954
00:43:09,000 --> 00:43:10,840
Your family of three,

955
00:43:11,000 --> 00:43:12,400
take a photo together.

956
00:43:12,800 --> 00:43:13,760
Zhang Guangrong.

957
00:43:14,240 --> 00:43:15,520
What brings you back so suddenly?

958
00:43:15,560 --> 00:43:18,400
The rumor about your wife
and Hu Sanyuan

959
00:43:18,559 --> 00:43:19,653
is spreading like wildfire.

960
00:43:19,720 --> 00:43:20,880
I want to tell him about it.

961
00:43:20,930 --> 00:43:22,030
You can't.

962
00:43:22,160 --> 00:43:23,000
Why?

963
00:43:24,520 --> 00:43:26,160
What's all this about?

964
00:43:26,200 --> 00:43:27,880
Making room for the trainees.

965
00:43:27,880 --> 00:43:29,680
I told you long ago

966
00:43:29,840 --> 00:43:31,210
that place isn't safe.

967
00:43:31,240 --> 00:43:32,720
Find out what to do.

968
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
笙ｪWhen I woke up and turned back笙ｪ

969
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
笙ｪI wasn't sure where to go笙ｪ

970
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
笙ｪWe met and brushed past笙ｪ

971
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
笙ｪYour shadow drifted out of sight笙ｪ

972
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
笙ｪThe stove fire blazed in my dream笙ｪ

973
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
笙ｪLit up the tracks of pearly tears笙ｪ

974
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
笙ｪIn my dream, water sleeves flew笙ｪ

975
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
笙ｪHiding a lifetime of love笙ｪ

976
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
笙ｪThe Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage笙ｪ

977
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
笙ｪSpring water brewed strong wine笙ｪ

978
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
笙ｪSheep moved through the valley笙ｪ

979
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
笙ｪIt felt like a promise
from another life笙ｪ

980
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
笙ｪWhen I woke up and turned back笙ｪ

981
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
笙ｪI wasn't sure where to go笙ｪ

982
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
笙ｪIf I chose again, I'd still roam笙ｪ

983
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
笙ｪAll over this sunlit plateau笙ｪ

984
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
笙ｪThe dream ends; the curtain falls笙ｪ

985
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
笙ｪMoonlight washes off this stage makeup笙ｪ

986
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
笙ｪThe one in the mirror wears gray hair笙ｪ

987
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
笙ｪAlready sang all my joy and sorrow笙ｪ

988
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
笙ｪAlready shouted across Qinchuan Plain笙ｪ
